			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote3-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote3-23985_002_004">3.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Buscar ejemplos en <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/jer/29.11-13?lang=spa#10" target="_blank">Jerem&iacute;as 29:11&ndash;13</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/joel/2.32?lang=spa#31" target="_blank">Joel 2:32</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/philip/4.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">Filipenses 4:6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/15.8-11?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">1 Nefi 15:8&ndash;11</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.37?lang=spa#36" target="_blank">Alma 37:37</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote4-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote4-23985_002_004">4.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Al llevar a cabo la Expiaci&oacute;n, &Eacute;l se mantuvo en comunicaci&oacute;n con Su Padre mediante la oraci&oacute;n, tanto en Getseman&iacute; (v&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/22.39-44?lang=spa#38" target="_blank">Lucas 22:39&ndash;44</a>) como en la cruz del Calvario (v&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/23.33-34,46?lang=spa#32" target="_blank">Lucas 23:33&ndash;34, 46</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote5-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote5-23985_002_004">5.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/6.9?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">Mateo 6:9</a>; <a href="http://scriptures.byu.edu/getscrip.php?ID=33742">TJS, Mateo 6:10</a>, <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/11.2?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Lucas 11:2</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/13.9?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">3 Nefi 13:9</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote6-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote6-23985_002_004">6.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/jacob/4.4-5?lang=spa#3" target="_blank">Jacob 4:4&ndash;5</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/20.31?lang=spa#30" target="_blank">3 Nefi 20:31</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/27.9?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">3 Nefi 27:9</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.8?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">Mois&eacute;s 5:8</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote7-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote7-23985_002_004">7.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/6.9?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">Moroni 6:9</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.4-5?lang=spa#3" target="_blank">Moroni 10:4–5</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote8-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote8-23985_002_004">8.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Bruce R. McConkie, <span class="emphasis">A New Witness for the Articles of Faith</span>, p&aacute;gs. 380&ndash;381.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote9-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote9-23985_002_004">9.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/6.7?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">Mateo 6:7</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote10-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote10-23985_002_004">10.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/6.5?lang=spa#4" target="_blank">Mateo 6:5</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote11-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote11-23985_002_004">11.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/6.8?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">Mateo 6:8</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote12-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote12-23985_002_004">12.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.48?lang=spa#47" target="_blank">Moroni 7:48</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote13-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote13-23985_002_004">13.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/33.3?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">2 Nefi 33:3</a>; v&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/jacob/3.1?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Jacob 3:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/31.38?lang=spa#37" target="_blank">Alma 31:38</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/37.2?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 37:2</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote14-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote14-23985_002_004">14.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/17.21?lang=spa#20" target="_blank">Mateo 17:21</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/9.29?lang=spa#28" target="_blank">Marcos 9:29</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-cor/7.5?lang=spa#4" target="_blank">1 Corintios 7:5</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.22-23?lang=spa#21" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 27:22&ndash;23</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.46?lang=spa#45" target="_blank">Alma 5:46</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/27.1?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">3 Nefi 27:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.76?lang=spa#75" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 88:76</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote15-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote15-23985_002_004">15.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Uno de nuestros himnos dice que &ldquo;La oraci&oacute;n del alma es el medio de solaz que surge en el coraz&oacute;n y da eterna paz&hellip; de quien conf&iacute;a en su Dios en horas de soledad&rdquo; (<span class="emphasis">Himnos</span>, 79).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote16-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote16-23985_002_004">16.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Seg&uacute;n lo permita la ocasi&oacute;n.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote17-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote17-23985_002_004">17.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Encontrar&aacute; m&aacute;s ense&ntilde;anzas &uacute;tiles en el discurso de Dallin H. Oaks, &ldquo;El lenguaje de la oraci&oacute;n&rdquo;, en <span class="emphasis">Liahona,</span> julio de 1993, p&aacute;gs. 17&ndash;20.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote18-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote18-23985_002_004">18.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase el <span class="emphasis">Diccionario de la Lengua Espa&ntilde;ola, </span>Espasa Calpe S.A., 1998 Edici&oacute;n electr&oacute;nica. Versi&oacute;n 21.2.0 &ldquo;Am&eacute;n: Voz que se dice al final de una oraci&oacute;n&rdquo;, para expresar consentimiento o aprobaci&oacute;n. &ldquo;Del hebreo &atilde;<span class="emphasis">m</span>&aring;<span class="emphasis">n</span>, as&iacute; sea, as&iacute; es&rdquo;, ciertamente, en verdad, de &atilde;<span class="emphasis">man</span>, ser firme&rdquo;.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote19-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote19-23985_002_004">19.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/90.24?lang=spa#23" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 90:24</a>; cursiva agregada.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote20-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote20-23985_002_004">20.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.37?lang=spa#36" target="_blank">Alma 37:37</a>; cursiva agregada. V&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/26.39?lang=spa#38" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 26:39</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/26.22?lang=spa#21" target="_blank">Alma 26:22</a>. En <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-thes/5.17?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">1 Tesalonicenses 5:17</a>, hay una ense&ntilde;anza similar de Pablo.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote21-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote21-23985_002_004">21.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Aunque las palabras no sean <span class="emphasis">exactamente</span> las que &eacute;l dijo, las representan en forma fiel.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote22-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote22-23985_002_004">22.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">La operaci&oacute;n quir&uacute;rgica se realiz&oacute; el 24 de mayo de 1960.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote23-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote23-23985_002_004">23.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Ten&iacute;a estenosis (estrechamiento) de la v&aacute;lvula mitral, causada por un ataque previo de fiebre reum&aacute;tica.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote24-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote24-23985_002_004">24.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">El Se&ntilde;or dijo: &ldquo;Si pides, recibir&aacute;s revelaci&oacute;n tras revelaci&oacute;n, conocimiento sobre conocimiento&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/42.61?lang=spa#60" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 42:61</a>). Por ejemplo, en la secci&oacute;n 9 de Doctrina y Convenios el Se&ntilde;or explica que &ldquo;debes estudiarlo en tu mente; entonces has de preguntarme si est&aacute; bien, y si as&iacute; fuere, har&eacute; que tu pecho arda dentro de ti; por tanto, sentir&aacute;s que est&aacute; bien. &ldquo;Mas si no estuviere bien, no sentir&aacute;s tal cosa, sino que te sobrevendr&aacute; un estupor de pensamiento&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/9.8-9?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 9:8–9</a>). V&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/jacob/4.10?lang=spa#9" target="_blank">Jacob 4:10</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote25-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote25-23985_002_004">25.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/ex/15.26?lang=spa#25" target="_blank">&Eacute;xodo 15:26</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/deut/13.17-18?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">Deuteronomio 13:17&ndash;18</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/1-sam/15.22?lang=spa#21" target="_blank">1 Samuel 15:22</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/jer/26.4-6?lang=spa#3" target="_blank">Jerem&iacute;as 26:4&ndash;6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/omni/1.13?lang=spa#12" target="_blank">Omni 1:13</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/41.1?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 41:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/133.16?lang=spa#15" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 133:16</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote26-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote26-23985_002_004">26.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.15-20?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Jos&eacute; Smith&mdash;Historia 1:15&ndash;20</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote27-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote27-23985_002_004">27.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/89.1-21?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 89</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote28-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote28-23985_002_004">28.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/od/2.title?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Declaraci&oacute;n Oficial 2</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote29-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote29-23985_002_004">29.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <span class="emphasis">Church News</span>, 1&ordm; de agosto de 1998, p&aacute;gs. 3, 12; 13 de marzo de 1999, p&aacute;g. 9; 4 de marzo de 2000, p&aacute;g. 7; 24 de junio de 2000, p&aacute;g. 9.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote30-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote30-23985_002_004">30.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Hasta el Hijo de Dios soport&oacute; esa experiencia, &ldquo;diciendo: Padre, si quieres, pasa de m&iacute; esta copa; pero no se haga mi voluntad, sino la tuya&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/22.42?lang=spa#41" target="_blank">Lucas 22:42</a>). Tanto el Padre como el Hijo sab&iacute;an lo que deb&iacute;a hacerse.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote31-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote31-23985_002_004">31.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Con respecto a la obediencia a la ley divina, v&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/abr/3.25?lang=spa#24" target="_blank">Abraham 3:25</a>. Con respecto a la obediencia a los consejos sabios de padres amorosos, v&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/6.1?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Efesios 6:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/col/3.20?lang=spa#19" target="_blank">Colosenses 3:20</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote32-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote32-23985_002_004">32.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/hel/10.4-5?lang=spa#3" target="_blank">Helam&aacute;n 10:4&ndash;5</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote33-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-23985_002_004">33.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/122.7?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 122:7</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote34-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-23985_002_004">34.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/25.12?lang=spa#11" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 25:12</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote35-23985_002_004"><a name="-23985_002_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-23985_002_004">35.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><span class="emphasis">Hymns</span>, 337. M&uacute;sica compuesta por Joseph Parry (no se ha traducido al espa&ntilde;ol).</p>
			</li> </ol>
                                            
